    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There is no completion event triggered when doing the following:\r\n- Initialize completion popup.\r\n- Type to the point when popup just disappeared after most recent character. In this case completion is still active (if delete previous character, popup reappears).\r\n\r\n**Edit**: latest Vim (8.2, patches 1-2815) also has the same behavior, but as Neovim has the initial implementation of `CompleteChanged`, I decided to open issue here.\r\n\r\nSetup information:\r\n- `nvim --version`: NVIM v0.5.0, Build type: RelWithDebInfo, LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\n- Operating system/version: Ubuntu 18.04\r\n- Terminal name/version: Gnome Terminal\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- Create the following configuration file (for example, under 'completion-event.vim')\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nlet g:count_changed = 0\r\nfunction TrackCompleteChanged()\r\n  let g:count_changed = g:count_changed + 1\r\n  echo 'CompleteChanged #' . g:count_changed\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nlet g:count_done_pre = 0\r\nfunction TrackCompleteDonePre()\r\n  let g:count_done_pre = g:count_done_pre + 1\r\n  echo 'CompleteDonePre #' . g:count_done_pre\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nlet g:count_done = 0\r\nfunction TrackCompleteDone()\r\n  let g:count_done = g:count_done + 1\r\n  echo 'CompleteDone #' . g:count_done\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nau CompleteChanged * call TrackCompleteChanged()\r\nau CompleteDonePre * call TrackCompleteDonePre()\r\nau CompleteDone * call TrackCompleteDone()\r\n\r\nset shortmess+=c\r\nset noshowmode\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Run `nvim -u completion-event.vim`.\r\n- Type `aaa<CR>bbb<CR>`.\r\n- Initialize complete with `<C-N>` (`CompleteChanged` is triggered).\r\n- Empty completion suggestion with `<C-P>` (`CompleteChanged` is triggered).\r\n- Type `a` (`CompleteChanged` is triggered) and then type `c` (**no** event is triggered).\r\n- Type `<DEL>` to see that completion is still active (`CompleteChanged` is triggered).\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nNo completion event is triggered.\r\n\r\nAnimation of behavior:\r\n\r\n![neovim_completion-event-issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24854248/125478264-b1894b79-e95a-430e-b324-48766fae40a1.gif)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nSome completion event is triggered. More intuitively, it should be `CompleteChanged` as it does trigger when no item is selected.\r\n\r\n**Edit**: Maybe even more intuitive would be to stop completion at this point (and thus trigger both `CompleDonePre` and `CompleteDone`). But this is probably too drastical. Is this behavior (not stopping completion when typing one character beyond all suggestions) intentional, because I couldn't find any reference?",
